---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---
<DocsLayout title="OpenClaw Docs">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>OpenClaw documentation</h1>
    <p class="muted">A lightweight Astro-powered static site that explains what OpenClaw is, how it works, and how the core pieces fit together.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>What this site contains</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A plain-English explanation of the OpenClaw model</li>
    <li>Core architecture concepts</li>
    <li>How channels, sessions, and memory interact</li>
    <li>How automation works with cron jobs and heartbeat checks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why Astro</h2>
  <p>
    Astro is a nice fit here because it generates a static site, keeps the repo simple,
    and works cleanly with GitHub Pages.
  </p>

  <p>
    Start with <a href={`${Astro.base}/docs/how-openclaw-works`}>How OpenClaw Works</a>.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
